reviewText: I had this Sing Along Songs tape on VHS when I was a kid, so I was very excited to get it for my 18 month old daughter who just loves dancing to the songs in her favorite Disney movies.  She really adores being able to listen and dance to song after song rather than waiting for the songs to come up while watching whole movies.  And it's such a great deja vu feeling that really takes me back to my childhood when we watch this DVD.
summary: I loved it and now my daughter does too!
Title: N/A

reviewText: Featuring only one song from Peter Pan- "You Can Fly", this is a disappointing addition to the Disney Sing Along Songs collection.Other songs include The Beautiful Briny (Bedknobs & Broomsticks), Colonel Hathi's March (The Jungle Book), I've Got No Strings (Pinocchio), Step In Time (Mary Poppins), When I See An Elephant Fly (Dumbo) and The Merrily Song (The Adventures of Ichabod & Mr Toad), totalling only 7 songs.Granted, singing along to Colonel Hath's March is lots of fun, but overall this is a little disappointing. I'm sure it'll keep younger underdemanding kids occupied though. The average Disney Sing Along Songs video or DVD is excellent- thus making this Peter Pan Sing Along not quite average.
summary: Not Quite Average Peter Pan Sing Along
